body_html:
Yes, that's where you should move it.
Using the last command you can now compile the file libtensorflow_inference.so.
You probably already have multiple of those, each one optimized for another architecture.
But you need only this one (armeabi-v7a), which should be compatible with all architectures.
This native library should contain the ops you need and can be used by TensorFlow for Android.

body:
Yes, that's where you should move it.
Using the last command you can now compile the file `libtensorflow_inference.so`.
You probably already have multiple of those, each one optimized for another architecture.
But you need only this one (armeabi-v7a), which should be compatible with all architectures.
This native library should contain the ops you need and can be used by TensorFlow for Android.
